              "title": "Breaking change in no-js/js behavior moving from v2 to v3",
              "number": 1742,
              "url": "https://github.com/Modernizr/Modernizr/issues/1742",
              "body": "Modernizr v2.x removes out the `no-js` class and then **unconditionally** adds a `js` class, whether `no-js` was present or not.\n\nModernizr v3.x changes this behavior and will **swap** the `no-js` class with the `js` class.\n\nIf you send a document that does _not_ set the `no-js` class initially, this may lead to the rendering of the document completely breaking. \n\nThere is no migration guide that mentions this type of change. The API documentation for the new `enableJSClasses` option mentions: \"Whether or not to update `.no-js` to `.js` on the root element.\", but the actual entry in the 3.x release notes mentions: \"New `enableJSClass` build option, which determines whether or not to add js/no-js classes to the <html> element when Modernizr runs; true by default (#1385)\"\n\nThe behavior should either be rectified or there should be a much **much** more clear indication to users that are upgrading, that this behavior has changed.\n",
              "createdAt": "2015-11-02T08:46:53Z",
              "lastEditedAt": nil,
              "updatedAt": "2016-05-18T10:54:44Z",
              "assignees": {
                "totalCount": 0
