              "title": "Finer-grained selection for the inputtypes detect",
              "number": 2226,
              "url": "https://github.com/Modernizr/Modernizr/issues/2226",
              "body": "Currently, the inputtypes detect is all-or-nothing. However, the detection for the `range` type triggers a forced reflow in the browser (when profiling with 5x CPU throttling in Chrome, this detect takes 65ms to recalculate style and compute the layout). Paying this cost while I'm only interested in the `date`detection looks bad.\r\n\r\nWould you consider allowing to configure the list of types we want to detect instead of just all or none ?",
